	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=198065><span id=Guru>Hardryv</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>50 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.25]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Cleric only?&nbsp;&nbsp;The very notions smells of bias.  Bah- no more than any other pure caster.  Any guild is going to do it however they like at the end of the day, but clerics aren't the only providers in a raid -- that role can be filled up just like any other.<br><br>My highest is a Necro, but I've played many other classes as well and I read a lot.  My 2 cents:  Would the item be great for any class?...Yes  Should the item go to just any old class?...ABSOLUTELY NOT  The answer to the obvious riddle is &gt;&gt; pure casters &lt;&lt;.  Good focus effects, in particular MP4, can often be more useful and more desirable than disciplines, and MP4 is too valueable for them.  A melee clase in particular would make only partial use out of this item -- only a pure caster would see the full benefit of it.  Why be wasteful?  Giving this to a Warrior would be like giving the best melee damage weapon in the game to a pure caster just because it had +40 Int and Wis on it... wasteful... let them get those stats elsewhere.  Keep it efficient.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Safe journey,<br>-Hardryv<br>xev.Harbit (728153)<br>venril.Harenth (645730)</td></tr>
